Breadcrumbs, Filters & Wildcard Search Conditions (ServiceNow)

🔹 Breadcrumbs

Breadcrumbs appear at the top of a list and show the conditions currently applied to filter records.

Features
Displays active filter conditions.
Helps users understand how records are being filtered.
Conditions can be removed individually by clicking the breadcrumb.
Entire filter can be removed using Run or Remove All Conditions.
Benefits
Easy navigation through filtered records.
Quick modification of search criteria.
Improves user experience while working with large datasets.
Example
Active = True > Priority = 1

Each condition appears as a breadcrumb.

🔹 Filters

Filters are used to display only records that meet specific criteria.

Features
Filter records based on field values.
Supports multiple conditions.
Can be saved and reused.
Available in list views and reports.
Common Filter Operators
is
is not
contains
starts with
ends with
greater than
less than
Example
State is Open
AND
Priority is High
Benefits
Faster data retrieval.
Better record organization.
Simplifies reporting and analysis.

🔹 Wildcard Search Conditions

Wildcards allow users to search for partial values instead of exact matches.
Common Wildcards
% (Multiple Characters)
Represents zero or more characters.

Example:
inc%
Returns:
INC0010001
INC0010002
INC0001234
* (Contains Search)
Used in list searches to find records containing specific text.
Example:
*network*
Returns records containing the word "network".

🔹 Search Conditions Examples
Condition	Result
starts with "INC"	Records beginning with INC
contains "email"	Records containing email
ends with ".com"	Records ending with .com
Active = True	Only active records
Priority = 1	High-priority records
